The paper deals with computational topology and specifically with algorithms for computing homotopy groups of simplicial complexes. This falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.GT). The algorithmic aspect of the paper also suggests that it could be classified under data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.DM). Finally, the paper deals with the size and complexity of triangulations, which could place it under the category of computational geometry and topology (cs.GR).
